C++
A variable is some space reserved in memory, and it has a type, a name, and a value assigned to it
A pointer is a variable where the value is an address of what it is pointing to.
A pointer variable is also statically bound to be of a certain type. 

Python
Variable in Python are more like pointers.
Variable is a label that always points to an object in the memory heap.


